      • createIndex

        <T extends OracleElementBase> OracleIndex<T> createIndex(java.lang.String indexName,
                                                         java.lang.Class<T> indexClass,
                                                         Parameter... indexParameters)
        Generates an index with a particular name, for a particular class, and of a particular type.
        Parameters:
        indexName - the name of the index
        indexClass - the element class that this index is indexing (can be base class)
        indexParameters - a collection of parameters for the underlying index implementation
        Returns:
        the index created

      • createKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void createKeyIndex(java.lang.String[] keys,
                                                          java.lang.Class<T> elementClass)
        Creates an automatically maintained index for the given keys and element class. If the automatic index already exists, the index configuration parameters will be taken from the index metadata table.
        Parameters:
        keys - an array of keys to create the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.

      • createKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void createKeyIndex(java.lang.String[] keys,
                                                          java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                          Parameter... parameters)
        Creates an automatically maintained index for the given keys and element class. If the automatic index already exists, the index configuration parameters will be taken from the index metadata table.
        Parameters:
        keys - an array of keys to create the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.
        parameters - the parameters used by the indexing structure. If the index is already defined, this parameters will not be considered. To take into consideration the parameters for the creation of an index, first drop the existing index and recreate.

      • createKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void createKeyIndex(java.lang.String key,
                                                          java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                          Parameter... parameters)
        Creates an automatic indexing structure for indexing provided key for element class. If the automatic index already exists, the index configuration parameters will be taken from the index metadata table.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to create the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.
        parameters - the parameters used by the indexing structure. If the index is already defined, this parameters will not be considered. To take into consideration the parameters for the creation of an index, first drop the existing index and recreate.

      • dropAllAutoIndices

        default void dropAllAutoIndices()
        Drops all existing automatic indices (vertex and edges). This operation will delete the indexing structure and remove all index configuration parameters stored in the index metada table IT.

      • dropAllIndices

        default void dropAllIndices()
        Drops all existing indices. This operation will delete the indexing structure and remove all index configuration parameters stored in the index metada table IT.

      • dropAllManualIndices

        default void dropAllManualIndices()
        Drops all existing manual indices (vertices and edges). This operation will delete the indexing structure and remove all index configuration parameters stored in the index metada table IT.

      • dropIndex

        default void dropIndex(java.lang.String indexName)
        Removes an index associated with the graph.
        Parameters:
        indexName - the name of the index to drop

      • dropKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void dropKeyIndex(java.lang.String[] keys,
                                                        java.lang.Class<T> elementClass)
        Removes an automatic indexing structure associated with indexing provided key for element class. If there are no more indexed keys in the automatic index, all index configuration will be removed from the index metadata table and the index structure will be deleted.
        Parameters:
        keys - an array of keys to drop the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.

      • dropKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void dropKeyIndex(java.lang.String[] keys,
                                                        java.lang.Class<T> elementClass,
                                                        Parameter... parameters)
        Removes an automatic indexing structure associated with indexing provided key for element class. If there are no more indexed keys in the automatic index, all index configuration will be removed from the index metadata table and the index structure will be deleted.
        Parameters:
        keys - an array of keys to drop the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.
        parameters - the parameters used by the indexing structure. If the index is already defined, this parameters will not be considered. To take into consideration the parameters for the creation of an index, first drop the existing index and recreate.

      • dropKeyIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> void dropKeyIndex(java.lang.String key,
                                                        java.lang.Class<T> elementClass)
        Removes an automatic indexing structure associated with indexing provided key for element class. If there are no more indexed keys in the automatic index, all index configuration will be removed from the index metadata table and the index structure will be deleted.
        Parameters:
        key - the key to drop the index for.
        elementClass - the element class that the index is for.

      • getAutoIndex

        default <T extends OracleElementBase> OracleIndex<T> getAutoIndex(java.lang.Class<T> indexClass)

        Parameters:
        indexClass - the element class that the index is for.

      • getDatatypeClassFromValueObjForTextIndex

        default java.lang.Class<?> getDatatypeClassFromValueObjForTextIndex(java.lang.Object value)
        Gets the data type class from the given value object. This is the data type that will be used for text indexing.

      • getDefaultIndexParameters

        OracleIndexParameters getDefaultIndexParameters()
        Get the public default index parameters associated to this property graph. The index parameters provided here will be used when an automatic or manual index is to be created without an explicit specification of the index parameters.
        Returns:
        a OracleIndexParameters object.
